<s> The economy of Victoria is highly diversified : service sectors including financial and property services , health , education , wholesale , retail , hospitality and manufacturing constitute the majority of employment . <\s>
<s> Victoria 's total gross state product is ranked second in Australia , although Victoria is ranked fourth in terms of GSP per capita because of its limited mining activity . <\s>
<s> Culturally , Melbourne is home to a number of museums , art galleries and theatres and is also described as the `` sporting capital of Australia '' . <\s>
<s> The Melbourne Cricket Ground is the largest stadium in Australia , and the host of the 1956 Summer Olympics and the 2006 Commonwealth Games . <\s>
<s> The ground is also considered the `` spiritual home '' of Australian cricket and Australian rules football , and hosts the grand final of the Australian Football League each year , usually drawing crowds of over 95,000 people . <\s>
<s> Victoria includes eight public universities , with the oldest , the University of Melbourne , having been founded in 1853 . <\s>
<s> Immigrants arrived from all over the world to search for gold , especially from Ireland and China . <\s>
<s> Many Chinese miners worked in Victoria , and their legacy is particularly strong in Bendigo and its environs . <\s>
<s> Although there was some racism directed at them , there was not the level of anti-Chinese violence that was seen at the Lambing Flat riots in New South Wales . <\s>
<s> However , there was a riot at Buckland Valley near Bright in 1857 . <\s>
<s> Conditions on the gold fields were cramped and unsanitary ; an outbreak of typhoid at Buckland Valley in 1854 killed over 1,000 miners . <\s>
<s> In November 2006 , the Victorian Legislative Council elections were held under a new multi-member proportional representation system . <\s>
<s> The State of Victoria was divided into eight electorates with each electorate represented by five representatives elected by Single Transferable Vote . <\s>
<s> The total number of upper house members was reduced from 44 to 40 and their term of office is now the same as the lower house members — four years . <\s>
<s> Elections for the Victorian Parliament are now fixed and occur in November every four years . <\s>
<s> Prior to the 2006 election , the Legislative Council consisted of 44 members elected to eight-year terms from 22 two-member electorates . <\s>
<s> The centre-left Australian Labor Party , the centre-right Liberal Party of Australia , the rural-based National Party of Australia , and the environmentalist Australian Greens are Victoria 's main political parties . <\s>
<s> Traditionally , Labor is strongest in Melbourne 's working class western and northern suburbs , and the regional cities of Ballarat , Bendigo and Geelong . <\s>
<s> The Liberals ' main support lies in Melbourne 's more affluent eastern and outer suburbs , and some rural and regional centres . <\s>
<s> The Nationals are strongest in Victoria 's North Western and Eastern rural regional areas . <\s>
<s> The Greens , who won their first lower house seats in 2014 , are strongest in inner Melbourne . <\s>
<s> About 61.1 % of Victorians describe themselves as Christian . <\s>
<s> Roman Catholics form the single largest religious group in the state with 26.7 % of the Victorian population , followed by Anglicans and members of the Uniting Church . <\s>
<s> Buddhism is the state 's largest non-Christian religion , with 168,637 members as of the most recent census . <\s>
<s> Victoria is also home of 152,775 Muslims and 45,150 Jews . <\s>
<s> Hinduism is the fastest growing religion . <\s>
<s> Around 20 % of Victorians claim no religion . <\s>
<s> Amongst those who declare a religious affiliation , church attendance is low . <\s>
<s> Victoria is a state in the south-east of Australia . <\s>
<s> Victoria is Australia 's most densely populated state and its second-most populous state overall . <\s>
<s> Most of its population is concentrated in the area surrounding Port Phillip Bay , which includes the metropolitan area of its capital and largest city , Melbourne , which is Australia 's second-largest city . <\s>
<s> Geographically the smallest state on the Australian mainland , Victoria is bordered by Bass Strait and Tasmania to the south , New South Wales to the north , the Tasman Sea to the east , and South Australia to the west . <\s>
<s> Prior to European settlement , the area now constituting Victoria was inhabited by a large number of Aboriginal peoples , collectively known as the Koori . <\s>
<s> With Great Britain having claimed the entire Australian continent east of the 135th meridian east in 1788 , Victoria was included in the wider colony of New South Wales . <\s>
<s> The first settlement in the area occurred in 1803 at Sullivan Bay , and much of what is now Victoria was included in the Port Phillip District in 1836 , an administrative division of New South Wales . <\s>
<s> Victoria was officially created a separate colony in 1851 , and achieved self-government in 1855 . <\s>
<s> The Victorian gold rush in the 1850s and 1860s significantly increased both the population and wealth of the colony , and by the Federation of Australia in 1901 , Melbourne had become the largest city and leading financial centre in Australasia . <\s>
<s> Melbourne also served as capital of Australia until the construction of Canberra in 1927 , with the Federal Parliament meeting in Melbourne 's Parliament House and all principal offices of the federal government being based in Melbourne . <\s>
<s> More than 26,000 square kilometres of Victorian farmland are sown for grain , mostly in the state 's west . <\s>
<s> More than 50 % of this area is sown for wheat , 33 % for barley and 7 % for oats . <\s>
<s> A further 6,000 square kilometres is sown for hay . <\s>
<s> In 2003–04 , Victorian farmers produced more than 3 million tonnes of wheat and 2 million tonnes of barley . <\s>
<s> Victorian farms produce nearly 90 % of Australian pears and third of apples . <\s>
<s> It is also a leader in stone fruit production . <\s>
<s> The main vegetable crops include asparagus , broccoli , carrots , potatoes and tomatoes . <\s>
