<s> The unproven Riemann hypothesis , dating from 1859 , states that except for s = −2 , −4 , ... , all zeroes of the ζ-function have real part equal to 1/2 . <\s>
<s> The connection to prime numbers is that it essentially says that the primes are as regularly distributed as possible . <\s>
<s> From a physical viewpoint , it roughly states that the irregularity in the distribution of primes only comes from random noise . <\s>
<s> From a mathematical viewpoint , it roughly states that the asymptotic distribution of primes also holds for much shorter intervals of length about the square root of x . <\s>
<s> This hypothesis is generally believed to be correct . <\s>
