<s> Orientalism , as theorized by Edward Said , refers to how the West developed an imaginative geography of the East . <\s>
<s> This imaginative geography relies on an essentializing discourse that represents neither the diversity nor the social reality of the East . <\s>
<s> Rather , by essentializing the East , this discourse uses the idea of place-based identities to create difference and distance between `` we '' the West and `` them '' the East , or `` here '' in the West and `` there '' in the East . <\s>
